message.content: "cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE". The paper deals with visual question answering, which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, "cs.CV" (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and "cs.CL" (Computation and Language) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also uses deep learning techniques, which suggests "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) and "cs.LG" (Machine Learning) as likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves training neural networks, which could fall under "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
